	<H3 CLASS="center"><A ID="I"></A>
I
	</H3>


	<H4 CLASS="start center"><A NAME="329"></A>
329 Wild Boar is Prepared thus
	<BR><SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">
Aper ita conditur
	</SPAN></H4>

	<P CLASS="justify">
It is cleaned; sprinkled with salt and crushed cumin and thus left. The next day it is put into the oven; when done season with crushed pepper. A sauce for boar: honey&#8203;<A CLASS="ref" NAME="329ref1" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Apicius/8*.html#329note1
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,EdNote,WIDTH,180)"
onMouseOut="nd();">1</A> broth, reduced wine, raisin wine.

<DIV CLASS="prose">
	<P>
	<A CLASS="note" NAME="329note1" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Apicius/8*.html#329ref1
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">1</A>
<SPAN CLASS="manuscript">Lan.</SPAN>, <SPAN CLASS="manuscript">Tor.</SPAN> <SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">vel</SPAN> instead of <SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">mel</SPAN>.
</DIV>




	<H4 CLASS="start center"><A NAME="330"></A>
330 Another Way to Prepare Boar
	<BR><SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">
Aliter in apro
	</SPAN></H4>

	<P CLASS="justify">
You boil the boar in sea water with sprigs of laurel; when done nice and soft, remove the skin, serve with salt, mustard, vinegar.


	<H4 CLASS="start center"><A NAME="331"></A>
331 Another Way to Cook <SPAN CLASS="outquote">Sauce for</SPAN> Boar
	<BR><SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">
Aliter in apro
	</SPAN></H4>

	<P CLASS="justify">
Crush pepper, lovage, origany, seedless myrtle berries, coriander, onions; add honey, wine, broth and a little oil; heat and tie with roux. The boar, roasted in the oven, is masked with this sauce, which you may use for any kind of roast game.&#8203;<A CLASS="ref" NAME="331ref1" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Apicius/8*.html#331note1
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,EdNote,WIDTH,180)"
onMouseOut="nd();">1</A>

<DIV CLASS="prose">
	<P>
	<A CLASS="note" NAME="331note1" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Apicius/8*.html#331ref1
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">1</A>
<SPAN CLASS="manuscript">Tor.</SPAN> continues without interruption.
</DIV>




	<H4 CLASS="start center"><A NAME="332"></A>
332 Make a Hot Sauce for Roast Boar thus
	<BR><SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">
Jura ferventia in aprum assum facies sic&#8203;<A CLASS="ref" NAME="332ref1" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Apicius/8*.html#332note1
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,EdNote,WIDTH,180)"
onMouseOut="nd();">1</A>
	</SPAN></H4>

	<P CLASS="justify">
Crush pepper, cumin, celery seed, mint, thyme, satury, saffron, toasted nuts, or toasted almonds, honey, wine, broth, vinegar and a little oil.

<DIV CLASS="prose">
	<P>
	<A CLASS="note" NAME="332note1" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Apicius/8*.html#332ref1
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">1</A>
<SPAN CLASS="manuscript">Tor.</SPAN> <SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">In aprum uerò assum</SPAN>, indicating, perhaps, that ordinary pork also was prepared "boar style." <I>Cf.</I> ℞ No. 352</A>.
</DIV>




	<H4 CLASS="start center"><A NAME="333"></A>
333 Another Hot Sauce for Boar
	<BR><SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">
Aliter in aprum assum iure ferventia
	</SPAN></H4>

	<P CLASS="justify">
Pepper, lovage, celery seed, mint, thyme, toasted nuts, wine, vinegar, broth, and a little oil. When the simple broth&#8203;<A CLASS="ref" NAME="333ref1" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Apicius/8*.html#333note1
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,EdNote,WIDTH,180)"
onMouseOut="nd();">1</A> is boiling incorporate the crushed things and stir with an aromatic bouquet of onions and rue. If you desire to make this a richer sauce, tie it with whites of egg, stirring the <SPAN CLASS="whole">liquid</SPAN> egg in gently. Sprinkle with a little pepper and serve.

<DIV CLASS="prose">
	<P>
	<A CLASS="note" NAME="333note1" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Apicius/8*.html#333ref1
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">1</A>
Presumably the broth or stock in which the meat was roasted or braised.
</DIV>




	<H4 CLASS="start center"><A NAME="334"></A>
334 Sauce for Boiled Boar
	<BR><SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">
Ius in aprum elixum
	</SPAN></H4>

	<P CLASS="justify">
Real sauce for boiled boar is composed in this manner.&#8203;<A CLASS="ref" NAME="334ref1" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Apicius/8*.html#334note1
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,EdNote,WIDTH,180)"
onMouseOut="nd();">1</A> Pepper, lovage, cumin, silphium, origany, nuts, figdates, mustard, vinegar, broth and oil.

<DIV CLASS="prose">
	<P>
	<A CLASS="note" NAME="334note1" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Apicius/8*.html#334ref1
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">1</A>
<SPAN CLASS="manuscript">Tor.</SPAN> sentence wanting in other texts.
</DIV>




	<H4 CLASS="start center"><A NAME="335"></A>
335 Cold Sauce for Boiled Boar&#8203;<A CLASS="ref" NAME="335ref1" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Apicius/8*.html#335note1
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,EdNote,WIDTH,180)"
onMouseOut="nd();">1</A>
	<BR><SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">
Ius frigidum in aprum elixum
	</SPAN></H4>

	<P CLASS="justify">
Pepper, cumin, lovage, crushed coriander seed,


<A ID="p185"><SPAN CLASS="pagenum"> p185 </SPAN></A>dill seed, celery seed, thyme, origany, little onion, honey, vinegar, mustard, broth and oil.

<DIV CLASS="prose">
	<P>
	<A CLASS="note" NAME="335note1" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Apicius/8*.html#335ref1
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">1</A>
℞ No. 336<!-- DON'T LINK --> precedes this formula in <SPAN CLASS="manuscript">Tor.</SPAN>
</DIV>




	<H4 CLASS="start center"><A NAME="336"></A>
336 Another Cold Sauce for Boiled Boar
	<BR><SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">
Aliter ius frigidum in aprum elixum
	</SPAN></H4>

	<P CLASS="justify">
Pepper, lovage, cumin, dill seed, thyme, origany, little silphium, rather more mustard seed, add pure wine, some green herbs, a little onion, crushed nuts from the Pontus, or almonds, dates, honey, vinegar, some more pure wine, color with reduced must <SPAN CLASS="outquote">and add</SPAN> broth and oil.&#8203;<A CLASS="ref" NAME="336ref1" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Apicius/8*.html#336note1
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,EdNote,WIDTH,180)"
onMouseOut="nd();">1</A>

<DIV CLASS="prose">
	<P>
	<A CLASS="note" NAME="336note1" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Apicius/8*.html#336ref1
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">1</A>
Strongly resembling our <SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">vinaigrette</SPAN>.
</DIV>




	<H4 CLASS="start center"><A NAME="337"></A>
337 Another <SPAN CLASS="outquote">Sauce</SPAN> for Boar
	<BR><SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">
Aliter <SPAN CLASS="outquote">ius</SPAN> in apro
	</SPAN></H4>

	<P CLASS="justify">
Crush pepper, lovage, origany, celery seed, laser root, cumin, fennel seed, rue, broth, wine, raisin wine; heat, when done tie with roux; cover the meat with this sauce so as to penetrate the meat and serve.


	<H4 CLASS="start center"><A NAME="338"></A>
338 Shoulder of Boar is Stuffed in this Manner
	<BR><SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">
Perna apruna ita impletur&#8203;<A CLASS="ref" NAME="338ref1" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Apicius/8*.html#338note1
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,EdNote,WIDTH,180)"
onMouseOut="nd();">1</A>
	</SPAN></H4>

	<P CLASS="justify">
Loosen the meat from the bones by means of a wooden stick in order to fill the cavity left by the bones with a dressing which is introduced through a funnel. <SPAN CLASS="outquote">The dressing season with</SPAN> crushed pepper, laurel berries and rue; if you like, add laser, the best kind of broth, reduced must and sprinkle with fresh oil. When the filling is done, tie the parts thus stuffed in linen, place them in the stock pot in which they are to be cooked and boil them in sea water, with a sprig of laurel and dill.&#8203;<A CLASS="ref" NAME="338ref2" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Apicius/8*.html#338note2
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,EdNote,WIDTH,180)"
onMouseOut="nd();">2</A>

<DIV CLASS="prose">
	<P>
	<A CLASS="note" NAME="338note1" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Apicius/8*.html#338ref1
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">1</A>
<SPAN CLASS="manuscript">G.‑V.</SPAN> <SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">Terentina</SPAN>, referring to
	<A HREF="
E/Gazetteer/Places/Europe/Italy/Lazio/Roma/Rome/_Texts/PLATOP*/Tarentum.html
	"TARGET="princeps"
onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,1,WIDTH,165)"
onMouseOut="nd();">
a place in the campus Martius</A>, where the <SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">ludi seculares</SPAN> were celebrated. <SPAN CLASS="manuscript">Tor.</SPAN> <SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">recentia</SPAN>, fresh.

	<P>
	<A CLASS="note" NAME="338note2" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Apicius/8*.html#338ref2
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">2</A>
The dressing consisted principally of pork or veal pounded fine, seasoned as directed above, and tied with eggs, as if often prescribed by Apicius.
	<P CLASS="i1 b0 a0 justify">
To verify how little high class cookery methods have changed consult one of the foremost of modern authorities, Auguste Escoffier, of the Carlton and Ritz


<A ID="p186"><SPAN CLASS="pagenum"> p186 </SPAN></A>hotels, London and Paris, who in his "Guide Culinaire" presents this dish under its ancient Italian name of <SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">Zampino</SPAN>.
</DIV>




	<H3 CLASS="center"><A ID="II"></A>
II
	<BR><SPAN CLASS="smaller">
Venison [Stag]
	<BR><SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">
In cervo
	</SPAN></SPAN></H3>

	<H4 CLASS="start center"><A NAME="339"></A>
339 Sauce for Stag
	<BR><SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">
Ius in cervum
	</SPAN></H4>

	<P CLASS="justify">
Crush pepper, lovage, caraway<SPAN CLASS="emend">,</SPAN>&#8203;<A CLASS="ref" NAME="339ref1" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Apicius/8*.html#339note1
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,EdNote,WIDTH,180)"
onMouseOut="nd();">1</A> origany, celery seed, laser root, fennel seed, moisten with broth, wine<SPAN CLASS="emend">,</SPAN>&#8203;<A CLASS="ref" NAME="339ref2" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Apicius/8*.html#339note2
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,EdNote,WIDTH,180)"
onMouseOut="nd();">2</A> raisin wine and a little oil. When boiling bind with roux; the cooked meat immerse in this sauce <SPAN CLASS="outquote">braise</SPAN> to penetrate and to soften, and serve. For broad horn deer as well as for other venison follow similar methods and use the same condiments.

<DIV CLASS="prose">
	<P>
	<A CLASS="note" NAME="339note1" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Apicius/8*.html#339ref1
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">1</A>
<SPAN CLASS="manuscript">Tor.</SPAN> <SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">carenum</SPAN>; <SPAN CLASS="manuscript">Hum.</SPAN> <SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">legendum: careum</SPAN>.

	<P>
	<A CLASS="note" NAME="339note2" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Apicius/8*.html#339ref2
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">2</A>
Wanting in <SPAN CLASS="manuscript">Tor.</SPAN>
</DIV>




	<H4 CLASS="start center"><A NAME="340"></A>
340 Another Way&#8203;<A CLASS="ref" NAME="340ref1" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Apicius/8*.html#340note1
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,EdNote,WIDTH,180)"
onMouseOut="nd();">1</A>
	<BR><SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">
Aliter
	</SPAN></H4>

	<P CLASS="justify">
Parboil and braise the venison. Crush pepper, lovage, caraway, celery seed, moisten with honey, vinegar, broth and oil; heat, bind with roux and pour over the roast.

<DIV CLASS="prose">
	<P>
	<A CLASS="note" NAME="340note1" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Apicius/8*.html#340ref1
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">1</A>
<SPAN CLASS="manuscript">Tor.</SPAN> Another little sauce for venison.
</DIV>




	<H4 CLASS="start center"><A NAME="341"></A>
341 Venison Sauce
	<BR><SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">
Ius in cervo
	</SPAN></H4>

	<P CLASS="justify">
Mix pepper, lovage, onion, origany, nuts, figdates, honey, broth, mustard, vinegar, oil.&#8203;<A CLASS="ref" NAME="341ref1" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Apicius/8*.html#341note1
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,EdNote,WIDTH,180)"
onMouseOut="nd();">1</A>

<DIV CLASS="prose">
	<P>
	<A CLASS="note" NAME="341note1" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Apicius/8*.html#341ref1
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">1</A>
Resembling a <SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">vinaigrette</SPAN>, except for the nuts and dates.
</DIV>




	<H4 CLASS="start center"><A NAME="342"></A>
342 Preparation of Venison
	<BR><SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">
Cervinae conditura
	</SPAN></H4>

	<P CLASS="justify">
Pepper, cumin, condiments, parsley, onion, rue, honey, broth, mint raisin wine, reduced wine, and a little oil; bind with roux when boiling.


	<H4 CLASS="start center"><A NAME="343"></A>
343 Hot Sauce for Venison
	<BR><SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">
Iura ferventia in cervo
	</SPAN></H4>

	<P CLASS="justify">
Pepper, lovage, parsley, cumin, toasted nuts or almonds, honey, vinegar, wine, a little oil; add broth and stir well.


	<H4 CLASS="start center"><A NAME="344"></A>
344 Marinade for Roast Venison
	<BR><SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">
Embamma&#8203;<A CLASS="ref" NAME="344ref1" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Apicius/8*.html#344note1
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,EdNote,WIDTH,180)"
onMouseOut="nd();">1</A> in cervinam assam
	</SPAN></H4>

	<P CLASS="justify">
Pepper, nard leaves, celery seed, dry onions, green rue, honey, vinegar, broth, add dates, raisins and oil.

<DIV CLASS="prose">
	<P>
	<A CLASS="note" NAME="344note1" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Apicius/8*.html#344ref1
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">1</A>
<SPAN CLASS="manuscript">Tor.</SPAN> <SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">Intinctus</SPAN>, same; a <SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">marinade</SPAN>, a <SPAN CLASS="whole">pickle</SPAN> or sauce in which to preserve or to flavor raw meat or fish.
</DIV>




	<H4 CLASS="start center"><A NAME="345"></A>
345 Another Hot Sauce for Venison
	<BR><SPAN LANG="la" CLASS="Latin">
Aliter in cervum assum iura ferventia
	</SPAN></H4>

	<P CLASS="justify">
Pepper, lovage, parsley, stewed Damascus prunes, wine, honey, vinegar, broth, a little oil; stir with a fagot of leeks and satury.&#8203;<A CLASS="ref" NAME="345ref1" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Apicius/8*.html#345note1
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,EdNote,WIDTH,180)"
onMouseOut="nd();">1</A>

<DIV CLASS="prose">
	<P>
	<A CLASS="note" NAME="345note1" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Apicius/8*.html#345ref1
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">1</A>
A fagot of herbs; regarding this method of flavoring<SPAN CLASS="emend">,</SPAN><!-- printed text has period --> <I>Cf.</I> notes to ℞ No. 277 <I>seq.</I></A>
	<P>
A sauce resembling our Cumberland, very popular with venison which is sweetened with currant jelly instead of the above prunes.
</DIV>



	<H3 CLASS="center"><A ID="III"></A>
III
	<BR><SPAN CLASS="smaller">
